[assistant] Fixed the native-image compile failure caused by JUnit’s native test registrar walking nested test classes and loading Byte Buddy internals that reference optional JNA.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changed:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Moved `UnsafeOverrideHarness` out of the public JUnit test class into a package-private top-level class.
[assistant] - Moved its helper `OverrideDispatcherClassLoader` to a package-private top-level class too.
[assistant] - This prevents `JUnitPlatformFeature` from recursively registering the harness as a nested test class and hitting `com.sun.jna.Library` while inspecting Byte Buddy superclass internals.
[assistant] 
[assistant] The test behavior remains the same; only the class layout changed to avoid native-image test discovery loading optional JNA-dependent Byte Buddy classes.
